The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Sen takes over as UBI chairman
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Sen takes over as UBI chairman
          OUR BUREAU                              
	Calcutta, March 1: Bhaskar Sen today took over as United Bank of Indias chairman and managing director following the retirement of S.C. Gupta on February 27. Prior to this, Sen was executive director of Dena Bank.         
	Sen started his career with Mumbai-based Union Bank of India in 1974 as a probationary officer. He has over 35 years of experience in India and abroad in various fields of commercial banking, including foreign exchange, credit, international banking, gold business, treasury, merchant banking and cash management services.        
	During his stint with Union Bank, Sen headed various controlling offices and was in charge of international banking divisions, gold business, merchant banking and cash management services, apart from holding independent charge of the treasury. He has also served as the head of new business, including overseas expansion and strategic initiatives, of Union Bank.         
	Sen was posted in IBU International Finance-Hong Kong (a joint venture finance company formed by Indian Bank, the Bank of Baroda and the Union Bank of India) and was one of its resident directors.                                                                                                                                       
